# {{PROJECT_NAME}} - Claude Instructions

## Rules

- **Protect user data:** Never `git stash`, `git reset --hard`, or `git checkout .` when `{{PROTECTED_DATA_DIR}}` has uncommitted changes. Backup first: `cp -r {{PROTECTED_DATA_DIR}} {{PROTECTED_DATA_DIR}}.backup`
- **Feature branches:** Never commit directly to `develop` for multi-commit work. Create `feature/<issue-number>-<desc>` from develop. Only merge when user approves.
- **One issue at a time.** Never work on multiple issues in parallel.
- **Human checkpoints are mandatory.** After build phases 1, 2, 4, 7 and after "Ready for testing" / "Ready for Prod" — STOP and wait for user.
- **Logs before code:** When debugging, use `/enable-debug` and check logs BEFORE investigating code.
- **Tests before merge:** Targeted tests must pass before merging to develop. Full suite (core + ui + e2e) must pass before merging to main.
- **Never release without explicit user confirmation.**
- **Never read** `node_modules/`, `__pycache__/`, `target/`, `dist/`, `.next/`, `.svelte-kit/`
- **Build phases are sequential.** Never skip phases or run them out of order.

