## Phase A — Build Pipeline

7-phase agent orchestration to build a desktop application from a Product Brief. Each phase invokes specialized agents that produce documents or code.

### Phase Overview

| Phase | Name | Agent(s) | Output | Model | Checkpoint |
|-------|------|----------|--------|-------|------------|
| 1 | Discovery & Specification | `product-analyst` | `docs/PRD.md` | opus | STOP |
| 2 | Architecture & Design | `solution-architect` + `database-architect` | `docs/architecture/`, `docs/database/` | opus | STOP |
| 3 | Desktop UI Design | `ui-designer` | `docs/design/` | opus | — |
| 4 | Implementation | `core-dev` + `ui-dev` + `integration-glue` | Source code | sonnet | STOP |
| 5 | Quality Assurance | `test-writer` + `security-auditor` | Tests, `docs/qa/`, `docs/security/` | sonnet | — |
| 6 | Build & Distribution | `devops-engineer` | Packaging, CI/CD, `docs/devops/` | sonnet | — |
<!-- LOCAL_DOCS_START -->
| 7 | Documentation & Delivery | `technical-writer` | `README.md`, `docs/developer-guide.md` | sonnet | STOP |
<!-- LOCAL_DOCS_END -->
<!-- NOTION_START -->
| 7 | Documentation & Delivery | main thread (Notion MCP) | Notion documentation database | sonnet | STOP |
<!-- NOTION_END -->

### How to Use

```
/build-phase 1       → Discovery: produces PRD.md → STOP
/build-validate 1    → User validates PRD → unlocks phase 2
/build-phase 2       → Architecture: produces architecture/ + database/ → STOP
/build-validate 2    → User validates architecture → unlocks phases 3-4
/build-phase 3       → Desktop UI Design: produces design/
/build-phase 4       → Implementation (Agent Teams): source code → STOP
/build-validate 4    → User smoke-tests the app → unlocks phases 5-7
/build-phase 5       → QA: tests + security report
/build-phase 6       → Build & Distribution: packaging + CI/CD
/build-phase 7       → Documentation: README, guides → STOP
/build-validate 7    → Final delivery accepted → transitions to Phase B
```

### Phase Dependencies

```
Phase 1 → [validate] → Phase 2 → [validate] → Phase 3
                                              → Phase 4 → [validate] → Phase 5
                                                                      → Phase 6 → Phase 7 → [validate] → Phase B
```

